    "title" : "IntelliJ hides my Java files after project opens",
    "body" : "<p>When I open my project in IntelliJ IDEA, at first I see all my Java files. But after a few seconds, they disappear from the Project view. The files are still present on disk, but in IntelliJ I only see pom.xml, .gitignore, README.md. The .idea folder looks fine. Why does IntelliJ hide my source files and how can I fix this?</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/HnhAaAOy.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/HnhAaAOy.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a>\n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/F0kDU7WV.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/F0kDU7WV.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n",
