    "question_id" : 79773032,
    "body" : "<p>IntelliJ Idea chooses to index the project every now and then and the project structure becomes broken for unknown reason. I also don't understand what is going on.</p>\n<p>However, it is easy to get in on the right path. Expand the circular arrows menu in Maven and select &quot;Sync All Maven Projects&quot; that runs the synchronization and it should fix the project structure browser as well.</p>\n<p>As a back-up, there is &quot;Reload All Maven Projects&quot; that does the full sync, unlike the previous option that is only incremental, though sufficient in most of the cases.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/pBm3aauf.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/pBm3aauf.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n",
